\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Creation of Users\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Creation of Metrics\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Creation of a Survey\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Proposal of a Process\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Performance of that Process (with optional oversight)\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Cross-cutting concerns throughout each phase of this process are 
\i data security
\i0  and 
\i access control
\i0 . 
\i Simplicity and ease of use
\i0  are important concerns. 
\i Reusability of content
\i0  (metrics and surveys) is a desirable feature. 
\i Aggregate/historical analysis of evaluations
\i0  is a desirable feature as well.\
\

\i It may not be possible to address all of these concerns and features in the CTEC Class Project.
\i0 \
\
\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\'96\
\

\b Access Control
\b0 \
\
A reasonably simple access control system is desirable. Such a system can borrow design elements from the standard ACS model in linux.\
\
Each user will be the default owner of any assets he/she creates (i.e. metrics and surveys). An owner may transfer ownership of any asset to another user.\
\
