\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf0 A Question contains the text of a question each peer is expected to answer.
\f1 \
\
Question\
	ID	TEXT PRIMARY KEY\
	version	Version:ID\
	text	TEXT\
\

\f0 A ChoiceList contains an encoded list of grades or other discrete values for each question.
\f1 \
\
ChoiceList\
	ID	TEXT PRIMARY KEY\
	version	Version:ID\
	list	TEXT (encoding of ordered list of strings)\
\

\f0 A User may create Surveys which will be presented to peer Users in a peer review Process.\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \
Survey\
	ID	TEXT PRIMARY KEY\
	version	Version:ID\
	title	TEXT\
	items	TEXT (encoding of ordered list of SurveyItem:IDs)\
\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf0 A Survey will contain one or more SurveyItems. Each SurveyItem comprises a Question, a ChoiceList and one or more optional evaluation types. 
\f1 \
\
SurveyItem\
	ID	INTEGER PRIMARY KEY\
	question	Question:ID\
	choices	ChoiceList:ID\
	[explanation	BOOLEAN (default = TRUE)]\
\

\f0 An Version record is created each time an existing Question, ChoiceList, or Survey is edited, including an initial Version record when the first edition is created. All Versions of the same Question, ChoiceList, or Survey will point to an Asset:ID, identifying them as versions of the same Asset. 
\f1 \
\
Version\
	ID	TEXT PRIMARY KEY\
	asset	Asset:ID\
	version	TIMESTAMP\
	latest	BOOLEAN\
	owner	User:ID\
	private	BOOLEAN (default = TRUE)\
\

\f0 An Asset record is created for every new Question, new ChoiceList, and new Survey. All Versions of this Question, ChoiceList, or Survey will point to this Asset:ID, identifying them as Versions of the same Asset. \
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \
Asset\
	ID	INTEGER PRIMARY KEY\
\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf0 A Process record contains all information needed by the system to administer/manage a peer review process.
\f1 \
\
Process\
	ID	TEXT PRIMARY KEY\
	survey	Survey:ID\
	begin	TIMESTAMP\
	end	TIMESTAMP\
	invitation	TEXT\
	status	'proposed', 'cancelled', 'running', 'completed'\
\

\f0 A Process record links a User to a Process, and identifies the role(s) of that user in the Process. When a Process is proposed, a Process_User record is created for every User involved in that Process, specifying their role and permissions.
\f1 \
\
Process_User\
	process	Process:ID\
	user	User:ID\
	accepted	BOOLEAN\
	overseer	BOOLEAN\
	peer	BOOLEAN\
\

\f0 When a Process is accepted, an Evaluation record is created for the Cartesian product of peers (each reviewer-reviewee pair), and for each of these pairs an EvaluationItem record is created for every SurveyItem of the Survey associated with the Process.\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \
Evaluation\
	ID	INTEGER PRIMARY KEY\
	process	Process:ID\
	[anonymous	BOOLEAN]\
	reviewer	User:ID\
	reviewee	User:ID\
	complete	BOOLEAN (default = FALSE)
\f0 \

\f1 \
EvaluationItem\
	evaluation	Evaluation:ID\
	item	SurveyItem:ID\
	choice	TEXT\
	explanation	TEXT\
\
\pard\tx712\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0 \cf0 Note: The 'choice' and 'explanation' fields in the EvaluationItem record could be broken out into separate tables. This breakout might be preferable when/if other types of responses (audio/video comments, documents, etc.) are facilitated in future versions of the system. For purposes of this CTEC227 version we can simplify by integrating both types of responses into the EvaluationItem records.\
